BOMB
  Order planes to bomb enemy or neutral sectors or ships.

SYNTAX
  bomb <plane-spec> <target-x,y> <type>

DESCRIPTION
  Sends planes on a bombing mission against a target.  Planes must
  be in an airfield within range of the target.

  <plane-spec>  - plane uid, range, or * for all eligible planes
  <target-x,y>  - the target sector or ship location
  <type>        - 's' for strategic (sector), 't' for tactical (units)

  Strategic bombing damages the sector's efficiency and stockpiles.
  Tactical bombing targets land units and ships in the sector.

  Planes use fuel (petrol) and suffer casualties based on AA
  defenses and enemy interceptors.  Planes must return to base
  after the mission; ensure the airfield is within range.

  Planes require at least 40% efficiency to fly.

EXAMPLE
  bomb * -3,2 s             all planes bomb sector -3,2 strategically
  bomb 0-3 2,4 t            planes 0-3 do tactical bombing at 2,4

SEE ALSO
  fly  launch  mission  build  attack
